      <tr>
        <td width="100%"><P>1.  BE on time.<br>
&nbsp;<BR>2.  If you can't be on time, get to the zone (or 
appropriate location before you camp out the day/night before).  If this is for 
ToV, get to Western Wastes, preferably right outside the zone in (loc to ToV is 
p600 p700). <br>
        <BR>3.  For major raids (raids that will take more than one night), 
bind as close to the raid location as possible.  If you are melee type, at the 
nearest town bindpoint, in case there is a need to break into a zone (example - 
Bind in Ogguk if going to Plane of Fear, etc).  If you are a caster, bind 
outside the zone in (example, at the ramp to the Fear portal, if going to Fear). 
<BR><br>
        4.  Make sure you know what items have a chance to drop in the zone.  For 
the most part, items will be randomed to those that can use it.  Exceptions will 
be ToV (see separate loot table), and zones as the Raid Master/Guild Leader see 
fit to set up a loot list prior to the raid. <BR><br>
        5.  Make sure you have full 
resist gear. See our enchanters for details as to what you need.  Attempt to 
gather the necessary supplies (drop gems, bars of  electrum, silver, gold, platinum, velium as needed.<br>
&nbsp;<BR>6.  Make sure you 
have a gate potion if you are a melee class.   This uses pottery tradeskill and 
        will take about 90 minutes of clicking (and no more than 50p).&nbsp; 
        Recipe for the Velium Vial can be found <a href="skills/Recipes.htm">here</a>.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
        You can ask most anyone in the guild as to the best way to get your 
        skill up there.&nbsp; Ignore the trivial as stated on the website, it is 
        actually around 130 or so.&nbsp; A path to skill up in pottery can be 
        found <a href="skills/TradeSkills.htm">here</a>. <BR><br>
        7.  
Invisibility/Shrink/SoW/Other potions - see the Shamen in the guild about useful 
potions. 
